values: wow.. it's been interesting these past few months.. if you all didn't know, Billy and I are going out now, and has been almost 2 months.. i have never been happier.. its great :-D  This weekend my family is down from pittsburgh visiting, and touring DC.. I went with them on saturday.  It was ungodly hot, and then I had to come home and go to work from 5:30 - 12.  crazyness. Nicole and I are talking again, which is great.. i missed the girl.  I went to myrtle beach with Brenna Lyn, and of course had a blast.. we don't talk too much anymore, im hoping that its because my family is here, so I really can't talk to anyone.  I love that girl <3  These past 2 months have been great between Billy & I.  For a while, we didn't see each other too much, which was hard, but we managed, and now we see each other a lot.. except for while im not here lol.  I'm leaving tomorrow for Pittsburgh with the family for a week, and then on the way there, touring Frostburg State University.  I'm actually very excited.. Hmm.. this entry was filled with a bunch of random stuff, but I just thought i'd fill everyone in on my life since i haven't in like 8724398 years lol.

hmm.. i try not to complain too often, but lately i dont know, something is wrong, and i just cant seem to make it right.

not sure, but recently ive been feeling.. empty.  i feel like my friends are only there to be there, i dont know, its like im completely alone.  I really dont understand the feeling, i mean, i know i have great friends, but sometimes it seems like im just there, and i cant seem to fill this empty space inside of me.  It's almost like a part of me is missing, ive felt it before, but it seems like lately its been there a lot, or maybe i just notice it more now.  In a lot of cases it feels like i cant tell my friends or anyone close to me anything because im afraid of being judged or that im overreacting.  but i also feel, not used, but just like i could be replaced anytime by anyone.  that feeling really sucks. almost like no1 really cares enough about how i feel to even notice it.  ive been trying lately to be nicer to everyone and trying to compliment everyone on lots of stuff, but it seems sometimes like what i do isnt good enough, or like it doesnt matter to anyone what i think.  i dont know, maybe i am overreacting, but maybe im not.  Maybe it's just because i always feel the constant need to impress and meet everyone's standards.  maybe im trying to be too good of a friend.  maybe i try too hard to be someone i'm not.  Not sure, maybe one day i'll find out, but until then ill keep it inside like always...

...whoever reads this, thanks for listening to my complaints.

hmm.. today was kinda weird.. in 1st period we were talking about life, and ambitions.  Ms. Searfoss made some really good points about how you should always live your life to the fullest because you never know when you wont be able to do that anymore.  It made me think all day.  I thought about how it is true that you should always tell people that you love them because if you dont, you may not ever get the chance to and then you will regret it.  And also, when you really want to do something or feel that you really should and you pass up the opportunity because you feel that there will be another.. that really made me think about how many times i've done that.  I mean honestly, what if you fell in love tomorrow, and you were too scared to tell the person that you love about it.. and secretly they loved you back.. what would you do if you went on living life with them not knowing and you never knowing how much you really loved them.  That could pass up so many opportunities, its just crazy.  Anyhow, I also wanted to say I love you to everyone.  I know I dont say this as much as i probably should, but I really do. 

on a happier note, i got to wear my new Roethlisberger jersey today.. anthony in my geometry class developed another nick name.. its "lil berger" =D im telling you, im marrying ben one of these days <3  hehe.  Anywho.. we got all our stuff for our science fair project from walmart and mcconnell pool place.  Its gonna be cool.. well as cool as science fair projects can be=P

yeah, today was the day.  After 7 months, 2 weeks and 6 days, a million fights, a billion "i love you's", 1 break, many good times, its over.  It hurts so bad.  More than I can explain.  It isn't anyones fault, no1 did anything wrong (even though he blames it on himself), it isnt near his fault.  I know we've had our share of arguements, and that break hurt too, but not nearly as bad.  I just really need a few days to clear my head.  It seems like everything is hitting me at once and it hurts so bad.  After sitting on the fone w/ us crying for about 30 minutes I realized just how much I really love him.  He has taught me so much over the past months and I cant even begin to explain how thankful and grateful I am for having a person like him in my life.  There are so many people who always think will is about laughing and joking and is annoying, but you don't know the real him.  He is nothing like that, and I was the one lucky enough to have him. I was his first love, and I broke up with him.  I broke his heart, and I can't do anything to change it.
